&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt; &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amazing people&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The National Health Service Blood and Transplant Tissue Services are an integral part of the NHS. Our Tissue Donation Programme saves and radically improves hundreds of lives every year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have NVQ level 3 in Care or Science or 4 GCSE’s at Grade C or above including English and Maths (or equivalent). You will also need to be able to retrieve multiple tissues from newly deceased donors. You must have good IT and organisational skills as you will have considerable administrative duties. A valid driving license is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are able to work evenings and weekends within a 7 day scheduled rota, we’d like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will start work with NHSBT as a Retrieval Assistant (Band 3 - £19,737 to £21,142) and will then progress to Senior Retrieval Assistant (Band 4 – £21,892 to £24,157) following successful completion of your training – we anticipate this will take 6-12 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Blood and Transplant (NHSBT) offers a dynamic and friendly working environment where teamwork is highly valued. Personal development is also considered a priority and is supported through extensive training and development opportunities open to all employees.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working towards equal opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
